Police in Embu are investigating the brutal murder of a primary school head teacher outside his house. Patrick Njeru, 48, was Riaguu Primary School headmaster.He was killed in his Muthatari village home in Embu West subcounty on Monday night.Embu West police boss Francis Sang said Njeru was entering his house at 7.15pm, when he was attacked.He said the head teacher was hit in the head twice with a blunt object. No one has been arrested.Sang said the killers did not steal anything from Njeru as his wallet and phone were intact.He said the head teacher has been having constant wrangles with his wife and they had separated.The body was taken to Gakwegori Funeral Home.